"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Fix: Context compaction resets CheckpointTranscriptStart causing stale carry-forward\n\n## Context\n\n`TestRapidSequentialCommits` fails for Gemini because context compaction events (`pre-compress` hooks) unconditionally reset `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0` in `lifecycle.go:410`. The Gemini transcript file grows monotonically (never truncated during compaction), so this reset causes stale files to re-appear in carry-forward.\n\n### Why the reset is wrong\n\nGemini CLI fires `pre-compress` after **every tool call** as part of its standard `after-tool → pre-compress → before-model` pipeline. The E2E logs show it firing 8 times (once per tool call) with only ~10K tokens. The transcript file shows zero evidence of actual compression: all 9 messages are intact, no lines removed, no compaction summary entry inserted. These `pre-compress` events are **no-ops** transcript-wise.\n\nThe handler unconditionally resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0` on every `pre-compress`, even when no compression actually occurred. This causes subsequent `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` calls to re-scan already-condensed messages.\n\n### Failure timeline (from `entire.log` and transcript)\n\nTranscript: 9 messages — msg 2: `write_file red.md`, msg 4: `write_file blue.md`, msg 6: `write_file green.md`.\n\n1. **Commit 1 (red.md)**: `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(offset=0)` → `[\"docs/red.md\"]`. Condensation → `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 3`\n2. **Compaction (`pre-compress`)**: resets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0`\n3. **Commit 2 (blue.md)**: `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(offset=0)` re-scans ALL msgs → `[\"docs/red.md\",\"docs/blue.md\"]`. `subtractFilesByName` removes blue → carry-forward `[\"red.md\"]`\n4. **Commit 3 (green.md)**: `FilesTouched = [\"docs/red.md\"]`, committed=`{\"docs/green.md\"}` → no overlap → `should_condense: false` → shadow branch persists → **test fails**\n\n## Fix\n\n### 1. Remove unconditional transcript offset reset in compaction handler\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:410`\n\nRemove:\n```go\nsessionState.CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0\n```\n\nAlso update the stderr message to remove \"transcript offset reset\".\n\nIn this test, `pre-compress` fires as a no-op — no actual compression occurs, so the offset should not be reset. We have no evidence of what a *real* Gemini compaction would do to the on-disk transcript (truncate, insert summary, etc.).\n\nRemoving the reset is safe because:\n- For no-op compactions (the observed case): offset remains correct\n- For real compactions that might alter the transcript: `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` handles offset > length gracefully (returns empty — the loop simply doesn't iterate), which is a safe default since those files were already condensed\n- If we later discover real compactions need special handling, we can add agent-specific logic at that point\n\n### 2. Update existing compaction test\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle_test.go`\n\nThe existing test `TestHandleLifecycleCompaction_ResetsTranscriptOffset` explicitly verifies the reset behavior. Update it to verify the offset is **preserved** instead.\n\n### 3. Add a unit test for the carry-forward scenario\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks_test.go` (or `manual_commit_test.go`)\n\nAdd a test that simulates the bug scenario: after condensation sets `CheckpointTranscriptStart = N`, verify that `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` only returns files after offset N (not from offset 0).\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass\n2. Run the failing E2E test: `mise run test:e2e:gemini TestRapidSequentialCommits`\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alex/.claude/projects/-Users-alex-workspace-cli--worktrees-1/8b761911-336c-4f6c-9756-df16fb765955.jsonl\n\n---\n\nrun our preflight f